Good news: Brooke came through with the phone, the rent, you name it!

493
00:34:10,263 --> 00:34:13,687
And Andy says as soon as finds out where Dan’s stashing the skimmed money,

494
00:34:13,990 --> 00:34:15,059
we can nail him.

495
00:34:16,924 --> 00:34:17,865
What’re you doing?

496
00:34:19,090 --> 00:34:20,278
I’m moving back home.

497
00:34:20,452 --> 00:34:22,034
And what is that, Dan’s bright idea?

498
00:34:22,312 --> 00:34:25,495
He’s right. Haley and I have been kidding ourselves this whole time.

499
00:34:25,592 --> 00:34:28,254
I’ve tried so hard to convince myself of otherwise but…

500
00:34:28,982 --> 00:34:30,283
I can’t pretend anymore.

501
00:34:30,502 --> 00:34:32,555
- Nah, this isn’t you talking.
- It is, Luke.

502
00:34:32,658 --> 00:34:35,888
I don’t wanna end up some bitter man who punishes Haley for what I could have been.

503
00:34:36,078 --> 00:34:37,630
She deserves better than that.

504
00:34:37,784 --> 00:34:38,536
So do I.

505
00:34:38,623 --> 00:34:39,897
No, you love Haley, Nathan!

506
00:34:39,975 --> 00:34:41,035
It’s not enough!

507
00:34:41,541 --> 00:34:42,257
Alright?

508
00:34:42,815 --> 00:34:46,303
Listen, I thought this marriage was gonna make both of our lives better…

509
00:34:46,538 --> 00:34:49,288
but all it ended up doing was getting in the way of our dreams and…

510
00:34:49,595 --> 00:34:53,035
Lucas, it’s time for me to focus, now; on basketball and my mom’s recovery.

511
00:34:56,451 --> 00:34:57,573
It’ll be better this way.

512
00:34:59,170 --> 00:35:00,521
Just don’t do this, man.

513
00:35:01,192 --> 00:35:02,754
Don’t let him win.

514
00:35:02,877 --> 00:35:04,769
I’ll do anything I can to help you.

515
00:35:04,868 --> 00:35:06,598
Then stop going after Dan.

516
00:35:08,007 --> 00:35:10,597
Lucas, I know the man’s no saint…

517
00:35:11,334 --> 00:35:13,248
but I think my mom’s ready to give him…

518
00:35:13,756 --> 00:35:15,918
ready to give our family another try.

519
00:35:16,895 --> 00:35:19,626
Nathan, you’re not that naïve, you know Dan’ll never change.

520
00:35:19,687 --> 00:35:21,074
You may be right, but…

521
00:35:22,190 --> 00:35:24,233
I owe it to my mom to give this a try.

522
00:35:24,811 --> 00:35:26,818
So can I count on you to back off?

523
00:35:33,501 --> 00:35:34,195
Yeah.

524
00:35:37,980 --> 00:35:41,851
And since all that cool new stuff went back to its home… my closet’s looking pretty bleak

525
00:35:41,922 --> 00:35:45,931
so I’m gonna shove all Lucas’ junk back in and then head to a movie.

526
00:35:48,078 --> 00:35:49,556
Hey, Peyton, was it worth it?

527
00:35:51,170 --> 00:35:52,587
Giving your heart to Jake?

528
00:35:54,155 --> 00:35:55,352
Absolutely.

529
00:35:55,587 --> 00:35:57,543
Even with the way things turned out?

530
00:35:57,938 --> 00:36:00,174
He’s in jail and you’re alone and hurting.

531
00:36:00,263 --> 00:36:04,706
But I’ve also been happier than I thought possible. So…

532
00:36:05,086 --> 00:36:09,034
I don’t know, I mean, being in love; that’s how you know you’re alive, right?

533
00:36:09,156 --> 00:36:13,472
Maybe. I’m starting to wonder how much one heart can take.

534
00:36:13,554 --> 00:36:16,743
Well, there’s only one way to find out, so just…

535
00:36:17,041 --> 00:36:19,852
call Lucas. It’s just a movie.

536
00:36:20,322 --> 00:36:24,143
Plus, wouldn’t you rather take a chance than always wonder what could have been?

537
00:36:29,407 --> 00:36:30,935
I’ll call you later, okay?

538
00:36:44,844 --> 00:36:45,934
Hey, Brooke?

539
00:36:46,004 --> 00:36:47,910
Hey, back atcha. You busy?

540
00:36:47,991 --> 00:36:50,274
Nah, I’m just grabbing some coffee. What’s up?

541
00:36:50,990 --> 00:36:54,007
We’ve been doing really well with this whole friends thing, right?

542
00:36:54,126 --> 00:36:55,350
Yeah, we have.

543
00:36:55,993 --> 00:37:00,039
Yeah, I think so, too. So, I wanted to ask you something.

544
00:37:00,418 --> 00:37:01,210
Um…

545
00:37:02,715 --> 00:37:03,905
Ah, hold on.

546
00:37:20,900 --> 00:37:22,158
Hey, Brooke, you still there?

547
00:37:22,485 --> 00:37:23,233
Yeah.

548
00:37:23,434 --> 00:37:24,293
Okay.

549
00:37:24,589 --> 00:37:25,696
What’d you wanna ask me?

550
00:37:32,680 --> 00:37:34,681
Let’s not screw this up, now, okay?

551
00:37:36,422 --> 00:37:37,139
Okay.

552
00:37:40,369 --> 00:37:41,301
Bye, Lucas.

553
00:37:56,933 --> 00:37:57,808
You okay?

554
00:37:58,596 --> 00:37:59,703
Yeah, I think so.

555
00:38:00,087 --> 00:38:01,372
Uh, why’d you wanna meet?

556
00:38:01,541 --> 00:38:05,560
Well, I’ve found out where at least ninety-five thousand of Dan’s skimmed money’s going.

557
00:38:06,139 --> 00:38:07,162
That’s great, where?

558
00:38:07,747 --> 00:38:10,772
Seems he’s been making a lot of small cash deposits…

559
00:38:11,162 --> 00:38:13,497
into a college fund. For you.

560
00:38:15,979 --> 00:38:18,335
I don’t get it. Why would he do that?

561
00:38:18,412 --> 00:38:21,350
He could be using the fund to hide the cash before he moves it elsewhere.

562
00:38:21,530 --> 00:38:25,375
Or… in some screwed-up way, maybe Dan really does care for ya.

563
00:38:28,032 --> 00:38:30,428
Look, Lucas, nobody knows about this, yet.

564
00:38:30,817 --> 00:38:33,490
If you want, I can just destroy the papers and call it a day.

565
00:38:34,243 --> 00:38:35,927
You wanna quit going after him?

566
00:38:36,219 --> 00:38:37,432
That’s your decision.

567
00:38:38,196 --> 00:38:41,780
I don’t know what I’m gonna turn up and I really don’t care. Dan’s nothing to me.

568
00:38:42,413 --> 00:38:44,017
Somebody’s gotta end it.

569
00:38:45,082 --> 00:38:46,884
He hurts everybody he touches.

570
00:38:47,758 --> 00:38:49,014
But he is your father.

571
00:38:50,146 --> 00:38:52,823
So, you tell me: do I keep digging?

572
00:38:59,003 --> 00:38:59,865
Yes.

573
00:39:02,147 --> 00:39:05,178
Don’t stop until you have everything.

574
00:39:06,780 --> 00:39:07,564
Okay.

575
00:39:22,368 --> 00:39:24,241
I thought you were going to see your husband.

576
00:39:25,797 --> 00:39:26,876
What husband?

577
00:39:56,342 --> 00:39:57,694
Sure this is what you want?

578
00:39:59,214 --> 00:39:59,943
Yeah.

579
00:40:00,792 --> 00:40:03,742
It’s gonna be great having you both here. You’ll see.

580
00:40:05,067 --> 00:40:07,587
Uh… actually…

581
00:40:08,751 --> 00:40:09,838
I’m moving home.

582
00:40:10,202 --> 00:40:11,114
What?

583
00:40:13,817 --> 00:40:15,675
Why? There’s plenty of room for all of us.

584
00:40:20,558 --> 00:40:21,533
It’s just time.

585
00:40:32,552 --> 00:40:33,308
Thank you.

586
00:40:33,909 --> 00:40:34,686
Any time.

587
00:40:37,504 --> 00:40:40,324
- I’m home.
- Oh, I’m so glad.

588
00:40:41,072 --> 00:40:42,028
Me too, mom.

589
00:40:45,034 --> 00:40:45,843
Hey, Brooke.

590
00:40:46,740 --> 00:40:47,482
Hey.

591
00:40:58,838 --> 00:41:03,691
Well, now that we are all here together, we need to set some new ground rules.

592
00:41:03,769 --> 00:41:05,650
I know that the two of you had a history.

593
00:41:05,734 --> 00:41:08,914
Oh, don’t worry, Karen, we’re just friends.

594
00:41:09,548 --> 00:41:10,674
Nothing more.

595
